-- Inca de Varas Seeks Permits for $100 Million Chile Solar Project
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2013-07-31T13:18:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-31/inca-de-varas-seeks-permits-for-100-million-chile-solar-project.html
Inca de Varas I SA,  the Chilean
renewable-energy developer, plans to build a $100 million
photovoltaic-power plant in  Chile ’s northern Atacama desert.  Work on the 50-megawatt project in the province of Copiapo
is expected to start in March, the Santiago-based company said
yesterday in a  filing  with Chile’s environmental licensing
agency Servicio de Evaluacion Ambiental.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at 
 snielsen8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  